# The intake grammar for the Loudon lion corpus (bench/loudon_lion_corpus.py) -- 50 verbatim
# sentences of Mrs. Loudon's *Entertaining Naturalist*, translated to CNL by an LLM with every
# sentence recorded (nothing silently dropped).
#
# Design: docs/design/homoiconic_grammar.md. This file is the honest test of the arc: the lion
# grammar in corpus/lion_grammar.cnl was written against 7 sentences chosen to exercise gaps we
# already knew about. This one is written against a corpus nobody wrote for us.
#
# PROTOCOL: written in ONE pass from the corpus VOCABULARY plus ordinary English constructions,
# before running it. Whatever it fails to cover is a real finding, not a grammar bug to quietly
# patch. bench/spike_loudon_grammar.py records the first-pass number.
#
# Beyond corpus/lion_grammar.cnl this adds: predicative adjectives (`the lion is strong`),
# copula-with-noun-phrase subsumption (`the lion is a cat`), and a second preposition (`at`).

# HEDGING (2026-07-20, the concept-inventory audit's most frequent gap -- sentences 8/12/13/18/24/37).
# A hedged clause is its OWN category (`hclause`), which is what keeps `clause asserts ...` from
# firing on it: a hedged sentence must NOT write an ink fact. `clause expands to hclause` only makes
# it reachable from the root and deliberately percolates NO slots. The band the hedge word denotes
# is NOT declared here -- it is the KB-level hedge lexicon (`uncertainty.hedge_bands`, `X means N`),
# the same scale the possibilistic layer already reads.

# ---- lexicon: closed classes ----
the is a determiner
a is a determiner
no is a negator
is is a copula
than is a comparator
in is a preposition
at is a preposition
generally is a hedge
usually is a hedge
sometimes is a hedge
occasionally is a hedge

# ...and the band each one denotes. Same surface as the KB hedge lexicon (`X means N`), and it must
# be declared HERE because the fold needs it as a compile-time constant (one rule per hedge word).
generally means 0.75
usually means 0.75
sometimes means 0.4
occasionally means 0.25

# ---- lexicon: content words ----
african is a modifier
asiatic is a modifier
bengal is a modifier
persian is a modifier
guzerat is a modifier
lion is a noun
cat is a noun
mane is a noun
tail is a noun
africa is a noun
asia is a noun
jungles is a noun
night is a noun
strong is a adj
smaller is a comparative
has is a transitive
roars is a intransitive
lives is a intransitive
hunts is a intransitive

# ---- productions ----
np expands to noun
np expands to determiner plus np
np expands to modifier plus np
np expands to negator plus np
np expands to np plus pp
pp expands to preposition plus np
vp expands to intransitive
vp expands to transitive plus np
vp expands to vp plus pp
vp expands to copula plus adj
vp expands to copula plus np
vp expands to copula plus ap
cp expands to comparator plus np
ap expands to comparative plus cp
clause expands to np plus vp
hvp expands to hedge plus vp
hclause expands to np plus hvp
clause expands to hclause

# ---- how each slot is filled ----
slot head in np from noun is only head
slot head in np from determiner plus np is right head
slot head in np from modifier plus np is right head
slot attr in np from modifier plus np is left head
slot head in np from negator plus np is right head
slot neg in np from negator plus np is left head
slot head in np from np plus pp is left head
slot prep in np from np plus pp is right prep
slot pobj in np from np plus pp is right pobj
slot prep in pp from preposition plus np is left head
slot pobj in pp from preposition plus np is right head
slot pred in vp from intransitive is only head
slot pred in vp from transitive plus np is left head
slot obj in vp from transitive plus np is right head
slot neg in vp from transitive plus np is right neg
slot pred in vp from vp plus pp is left pred
slot obj in vp from vp plus pp is left obj
slot prep in vp from vp plus pp is right prep
slot pobj in vp from vp plus pp is right pobj
slot adjc in vp from copula plus adj is right head
slot kind in vp from copula plus np is right head
slot cobj in cp from comparator plus np is right head
slot comp in ap from comparative plus cp is left head
slot cobj in ap from comparative plus cp is right cobj
slot comp in vp from copula plus ap is right comp
slot cobj in vp from copula plus ap is right cobj
slot subj in clause from np plus vp is left head
slot pred in clause from np plus vp is right pred
slot obj in clause from np plus vp is right obj
slot neg in clause from np plus vp is right neg
slot prep in clause from np plus vp is right prep
slot pobj in clause from np plus vp is right pobj
slot comp in clause from np plus vp is right comp
slot cobj in clause from np plus vp is right cobj
slot adjc in clause from np plus vp is right adjc
slot kind in clause from np plus vp is right kind

# the hedge itself, plus the ordinary clause slots carried through the hedged shape
slot hedge in hvp from hedge plus vp is left head
slot pred in hvp from hedge plus vp is right pred
slot obj in hvp from hedge plus vp is right obj
slot adjc in hvp from hedge plus vp is right adjc
slot kind in hvp from hedge plus vp is right kind
slot neg in hvp from hedge plus vp is right neg
slot prep in hvp from hedge plus vp is right prep
slot pobj in hvp from hedge plus vp is right pobj
slot comp in hvp from hedge plus vp is right comp
slot cobj in hvp from hedge plus vp is right cobj
slot subj in hclause from np plus hvp is left head
slot hedge in hclause from np plus hvp is right hedge
slot pred in hclause from np plus hvp is right pred
slot obj in hclause from np plus hvp is right obj
slot adjc in hclause from np plus hvp is right adjc
slot kind in hclause from np plus hvp is right kind
slot neg in hclause from np plus hvp is right neg
slot prep in hclause from np plus hvp is right prep
slot pobj in hclause from np plus hvp is right pobj
slot comp in hclause from np plus hvp is right comp
slot cobj in hclause from np plus hvp is right cobj

# ---- which slots become facts ----
# `hedges` is the possibilistic verb: the triple goes in PENCIL behind a fork banded by the hedge
# word, so a hedged sentence commits NO ink. `hclause` being its own category is what keeps the
# plain `clause asserts ...` lines from firing on it as well.
np asserts head is attr
clause asserts subj pred obj unless neg
clause denies subj pred obj when neg
clause asserts subj pred true unless obj
clause asserts subj prep pobj when pobj
clause asserts subj comp cobj when cobj
clause asserts subj is adjc when adjc
clause asserts subj is_a kind when kind
# The hedged counterparts. `hedges under hedge` says WHICH slot carries the band, once, so each
# line's own `when`/`unless` guard is free -- which is what lets the intransitive and prepositional
# shapes exist at all. These mirror the `clause asserts ...` lines above ONE FOR ONE: a hedged
# sentence must be able to say everything a plain one can, or the gap is silent (the sentence
# parses, routes as `fact`, and commits nothing).
hclause hedges under hedge
hclause hedges subj pred obj unless neg
hclause hedges subj pred true unless obj
hclause hedges subj prep pobj when pobj
hclause hedges subj comp cobj when cobj
hclause hedges subj is adjc when adjc
hclause hedges subj is_a kind when kind
